      • Fmz

        public Fmz()
        Constructor for firemanagement zones. Makes and initializes naturalfires, manmadefires, percentfires, cost arrays, then sets the acres, totalFirs, firesperacre, and suppression cost variables for this Fire Management Zone.

      • Fmz

        public Fmz(java.lang.String newName)
        Overloaded fire management zone constructor. Used to temporarily create a fmz object for use in creating new areas. sets the name to parameter names and makes the natural fires, manamade fires, percent fires, and cost arrays null.

      • duplicate

        public Fmz duplicate(java.lang.String newName)
        Used when loading areas. If the loaded fmz does not exist, then create one which has that name but is a copy of the default fmz. This way if a user later on loads an fmz data file the units fmz will get correctly mapped to the newly loaded version.

      • readData

        public static void readData(java.io.BufferedReader fin)
                     throws SimpplleError
        Parameters:
        fin -
        Throws:
        SimpplleError - Each line represents an FMZ. The line is comma delimited the fields are: name, id, acres, natural fires, manmade fires, cost. the last three fields are further subdived using colons. Note: The first line of the input file is the number of lines in the file.
